name: Ratchet
description: Ratchet is the primary series protagonist, being a very streetwise mechanic whose life was changed after meeting his robot pal Clank.

name: Clank
description: Clank is the primary side character, a practical and analytical robot who assists his friend Ratchet across their planet-hopping adventures.

name: Rivet
description: Rivet is a secondary protagonist from a dark-future alternate dimension where she is the underdog trying to take down the evil reign of King Nefarious.

name: Kit
description: Kit is a secondary side character, a small robot similar to Clank, however she is more reserved and unsure of herself as she assists Ratchet and Rivet.

name: Ann Takamaki
description: Fellow classmate the main character and Ryuji, Ann is one of the more popular students at Shujin Academy, but often dislikes the way that people only see her for her looks. While many see her as vapid, Ann is very intelligent, both academically and emotionally, often helping to mediate some group arguments.

name: Ryuji Sakamoto
description: While coming off as brash and loud, Ryuji is a very passionate athlete with a love of competition, as well as fiercely protective of his teammates' wellbeing. Ryuji's boisterous positivity often overshadows his lack of traditional smarts, but he's eager and willing to lend a hand if possible.

name: Morgana
description: Morgana is a strange being from the Metaverse, who takes on the form of a cat when accompanying the characters in the real world. While mysterious, he is the one who helps the main characters with navigating and fighting within the Metaverse to help take down society's corruption.

name: Yusuke Kitagawa
description: Very straightforward and to the point, Yusuke is an artistic prodigy in high school, and lived under the mentorship of his art teacher after his mother's passing. While he can be blunt and does not quite understand social cues well, Yusuke is loyal and passionate about what he believes in, seeing beauty in the world at every turn.

name: The Maiden in Black
description: The Maiden in Black tends to the Nexus, helping wandering souls seeking to restore balance to Boletaria. While not joining them in battle, she offers aid and a kind word to all who enter the sanctuary.

name: Batman
description: When he was a boy, Bruce Wayne's parents were killed in front of him during a robbery gone wrong. In response, he trained for years and used his vast family wealth to become Batman. He now uses his superior combat prowess and versatile library of gadgets to take down criminals in Gotham City.

name: Nathan Drake
description: While initially introducing himself as a descendant of the old explorer, Sir Francis Drake, Nathan soon reveals himself to be a treasure hunter through and through. Oftentimes relying on his wiles and charm to get him out of a sticky situation, Nathan knows hot to defend himself and will do

name: Victor Sullivan
description: A longtime treasure hunting partner and Nathan's mentor, Victor "Sully" Sullivan is getting on in years but nowhere near ready to throw in the towel if he smells a good treasure haul. While Nathan can argue that he's into treasure hunting for the adventure, Sully is more than happy to admit that the riches are his main motivator. Despite that, he is fiercely loyal to Nathan and would help him if needed.

name: Elena Fisher
description: An up-and-coming investigative journalist, Elena is looking for a good story that can catapult her career, and figures that Nathan Drake might have the story she's after However, as she gets swept up into the adventures with him, she shows that she is more than willing to follow him and his crazy story to its conclusion.

name: Prometheus
description: In ancient Greek mythology, Prometheus stole fire from the gods and brought it to humanity, being imprisoned as punishment. The game sees him during this imprisonment, but he takes on the role as the narrator, constantly being the main force rooting for the hero, Fenyx, throughout the story.

name: Fenyx
description: The main protagonist and hero of the game, Fenyx is a young, plucky character who seeks to rescue the gods of Olympus and save the world. Across the adventure, they interact with a number of the gods and monsters, but always manage to hold on to their wits and courage to see the quest through.

name: Hermes
description: The messenger of the gods, Hermes comes off as a very smug and occasionally abrasive fellow, but is a good guy deep down. Oftentimes coming in to tease and irritate Fenyx, he does offer a good deal of aid on their quest and wants to help.

name: Zavala
description: The current leader of the Titan Vanguard, Zavala has been living in the Last City nearly since it was founded, and feels it is his personal duty to protect those within. While he is a bulwark of courage, Zavala hides a tragic past and lost love, understanding deeply what will happen if he fails in his duties.

name: Ikora Rey
description: The current leader of the Warlock Vanguard, Ikora is one of the most gifted of her class of Guardian, but also the most conscious of the losses they have maintained. She carefully considers as many options as she can while coordinating Guardian operations, but isn't afraid to go into the field herself and deal with issues with her own powers.

name: Eris Morn
description: Formerly a Hunter, Eris lost her team after a failed mission to stop the Hive god Crota. It took immense willpower and dedication for her to escape, losing a part of herself in the process. Despite this, Eris has remained steadfast and offers aid to Guardians if she can.

name: Guardians
description: Not an individual, but a term for those resurrected by the Traveler and granted limited immortality. Guardians are born from the dead, resurrected with no memories of their past lives but gifted incredible powers to protect the Traveler and humanity. Whether running alone or in a fireteam, Guardians are adept at combat and coordination, able to defeat even the most impossible foes.

name: Toriel
description: Toriel lives peacefully by the Underground's entrance, maintaining her small home and offering pies and a kind word to anyone who stops by. She often seeks to help in other ways, and will offer protection to those she sees needing it.

name: Sans
description: The older brother to Papyrus, Sans is a very laid back jokester who takes life as it goes. However, this does not mean that he will lie back and let people walk over him. Sans has a great deal going on under the surface, but doesn't often choose to show it.

name: Alphys
description: The Royal Scientist of the Underground, Alphys is a very nerdy and timid monster. She would much rather spend her time inventing in her laboratory and reading comics than do much else. However, she has a strong desire to meet new people, but just hasn't had the right push to go for it yet.

name: Undyne
description: The current Captain of the Underground's Royal Guard, Undyne is fiercely protective of the Underground's inhabitants and will do whatever it takes to keep them safe from any perceived threats. Despite this hardened appearance, Undyne can be very dramatic and over the top, with a deep enthusiasm for what she enjoys showing her softer side.

name: Papyrus
description: The younger brother of Sans, Papyrus seeks to join the Royal Guard and serve under his best friend Undyne. Unfortunately, his enthusiasm does not translate into direct skill aside from cooking, but he is more interested in people getting along than fighting.

name: Cuphead
description: One of the two main characters, Cuphead can be impulsive and easily manipulated, but is willing to set things right if he messes up. He is Mugman's brother.

name: Mugman
description: One of the two main characters, Mugman is the more reasonable of the duo, but doesn't often think a situation through until the consequences are too apparent. He is Cuphead's brother.

name: Spyro
description: The main hero of the series, Spyro always seeks to stop the bad guy and save the day; however that doesn't mean he won't stop to have some fun doing it. While occasionally coming off as smug and overconfident, Spyro is more than willing to hand a hand if needed, but he may complain about it on the way.

name: Elora
description: A faun from the land of Avalar, Elora is an intelligent and emotionally aware individual who seeks to help Spyro in his adventures. Past her positivity and playfulness, Elora has a greater role in helping the people of her home and often offers insight and leadership.

name: Hunter
description: One of Spyro's allies, Hunter is a cheetah with a penchant for getting distracted. Despite this and his more laid back attitudes, he is eager to help Spyro how he can on his adventures, even if not fully understanding their importance. He's a welcome addition to the list of Spyro's allies despite his shortcomings.

name: Sparx the Dragonfly
description: Spyro's mostly silent travelling companion, Sparx is always there when Spyro needs him. He helps him out by collecting discarded items Spyro needs, and even keeping an eye on how Spyro is doing. Despite his small size, he can be quite heroic when the situation may call for it.

name: Mickey Mouse
description: The primary mascot of the Walt Disney Company, Mickey Mouse is an enthusiastic mouse with a long and storied history. Here, he finds himself causing mischief and accidentally wreaks havoc on the Wastelands, a home for long forgotten cartoon characters. Mickey is willing to help and make amends, fighting those out to stop him, and stopping the monstrous Phantom Blot creature to save the day.

name: Oswald the Lucky Rabbit
description: A long forgotten character, Oswald is the ruler of the Wastelands, but lives in isolation ever since the land was mostly destroyed in the Thinner Disaster. Having lost someone he loved, Oswald is not happy that he needs to help Mickey on the adventure, but there is still good left in him as he wants what is best for his citizens and the world.

name: Sora
description: The main character of the series, Sora is an eager kid from Destiny Islands who would love nothing more than to go on adventures with his friends: Riku and Kairi. He is also very competitive and aspirational, seeking to become the best he can be amongst his friends, but always lagging behind Riku. When it comes down to it, however, he puts rivalry aside to offer a hand to anyone who may need it, being very idealistic.

name: Donald
description: In the Kingdom Hearts universe, Donald Duck is the high wizard for King Mickey's court. Despite his tendencies for loud outbursts, Donald is focused on the task at hand and can offer some words of encouragement in the necessary circumstances.

name: Goofy
description: In the Kingdom Hearts universe, Goofy is the captain of King Mickey's royal guard. He is also very loyal to those he considers friends, especially the King. Oftentimes proving that he is much smarter and more observant than others realize, Goofy as direct as he is resilient.

name: Riku
description: One of Sora's longtime friends, Riku can be fiercely competitive and is the most athletic of the main friend group. He doesn't often brag about such things, but if given the chance, he's not the most humble about it. His ultimate dream is to leave Destiny Islands if given any chance to do so, wanting to explore what's outside of their small world.

name: Kairi
description: Kairi has only been friends with Riku and Sora for a short time, but has already cemented herself into their tight-knit group. While she doesn't remember much of her life before arriving at Destiny Islands, she prefers to focus on the fun of the present and enjoying her time with her friends.

name: Martin Septim
description: Last surviving, illegitimate son of the recently assassinated emperor, Uriel Septim VII, Martin has found his quiet life as a priest upended by the Oblivion Crisis. Now, he must take up his role as the new emperor, and find the power to master his draconic bloodline and stop the cataclysm from growing too dire.

name: Aloy
description: The main protagonist, Aloy has been an Outcast from her tribe her entire life, never being allowed to socialize with others from her tribe. After finding a forgotten piece of human technology in an ancient ruin, Aloy gains a fascination with the world that existed before and what may have happened to the long dead societies. Once getting the opportunity to prove herself and rejoin the tribe, Aloy goes off to investigate the strange, corrupting presence infecting the machines of the land.

name: Scrooge McDuck
description: The richest duck in the world, Scrooge McDuck has a vast wealth in his company, but is incredibly frugal and stingy. Along with this, he has a deep love for adventuring and treasure hunting, usually being followed around by his nephews: Huey, Dewey, and Louie. Despite his desires for treasure, he'll put his family first when the chips are down.

name: Launchpad McQuack
description: One of the most skilled pilots in every aspect of aviation, Launchpad only has one problem: landing. He works as Scrooge McDuck's driver and pilot, helping him get to wherever he needs to be.

name: Huey, Dewey, and Louie
description: The three nephews of Scrooge McDuck are rarely seen without one another, always working together as part of a team. They may bicker on occasion, but when it comes to it they'll be there to help one another.

name: Sarah Morgan
description: Leader of the secretive explorer's organization known as "Constellation", Sarah was handpicked by the previous leader to take over. An experienced soldier and pilot, she has been able to keep the organization on track over the past number of years in the search for greater mysteries in the universe. She also has a more fun-loving side, and isn't above making a snarky remark here or there.

name: Sam Coe
description: A descendant of one of humanity's pioneers, Sam has a many expectations put upon him because of his family name. However, he would rather look after his daughter in peace while exploring the galaxy. He hides a lot of unresolved guilt and regret for how his past relationship has gone, but wants to earnestly make amends in some way.

name: Barrett
description: A smooth talker and skilled negotiator, Barrett has been a part of "Constellation" for years, longer than most members due to his family being responsible for its founding. He always likes to talk like he knows more than he lets on, knowing it can ruffle some feathers of those around him, but he doesn't mind. He's taken to the stars in his later years, working to explore and unearth new discoveries.

name: Andreja
description: Formerly working with criminal organizations, Andreja has been trying to turn things around, but is constantly worried that it may come back to get her in the end. While oftentimes on edge, Andreja reveals a more sensitive side when her cautious exterior can be broken down. Earning her trust is difficult but worthwhile.

name: Sandy Cheeks
description: A squirrel who now lives undersea in her habitation dome, Sandy puts up with her friend Spongebob's silliness while still making time for her own pursuits around town; notably martial arts and rodeo.

name: Pac-Man
description: A yellow, rounded fellow; Pac-Man fights off ghosts by powering up and eating them in order to send them back to where they came from.

name: Peter Parker/Spider-Man

name: Mary Jane Watson
description: A journalist who works at the Daily Bugle, Mary Jane Watson will do what it takes to investigate and expose crime and corruption.

name: Noctis Lucis Caelum
description: The Crown Prince of the kingdom of Lucis, Noctis is next in line for the throne but would most prefer to spend his time with his close group of friends.

name: Prompto Argentum
description: One of Prince Noctis's best friends, Prompto sought to improve himself in order to feel deserving of spending time with others; he is most appreciated for his humor and perceptiveness.

name: Ignis Scientia
description: Ignis is one of Prince Noctis's closest friends and confidants, having spent a good portion of the prince's teen years as his personal tutor and chef; he is most appreciated for his frankness and culinary abilities.

name: Gladiolus Amicitia
description: Formerly the personal trainer and Prince Noctis's personal bodyguard, he is devoted to his friends and will leap to their defense at a moment's notice.

name: Lunafreya "Luna" Nox Fleuret
description: The Oracle to the Gods, Lunafreya has a deeply spiritual connection to the magic of the world of Eos; now she and Noctis are in a politically motivated arranged marriage that neither want, but she seeks to aid him in his quest regardless.

name: Desmond Miles
description: Desmond Miles is a down on his luck bartender, frustrated by his continuing loss of autonomy as his actions are heavily observed by the corporation Abstergo, but he intends to make things difficult for them.

name: Lucy Stillman
description: An assistant for Abstergo's Animus project, Lucy is Desmond Miles's handler with her own ulterior motives, never quite certain as to where her loyalties lie.

The Mona Lisa is housed in the Louvre Museum in Paris and is considered one of the most famous and valuable works of art in the world.

His versatility spanned various musical forms, including symphonies, operas, chamber music, and piano sonatas.

Jesters were also traveling performers who entertained common folk at fairs and town markets, and the discipline continues into the modern day, where jesters perform at historical-themed events. The jester in "All Along the Watchtower" represents a more carefree or whimsical outlook on life.

name: Bette Davis
description:
Bette Davis was an iconic American actress, often considered one of the greatest actresses in Hollywood history. Born Ruth Elizabeth Davis on April 5, 1908, in Lowell, Massachusetts, she had a prolific career spanning six decades, from the 1930s to the 1980s. Davis was known for her versatile acting abilities, intense performances, and distinctive voice.

Davis began her acting career in theater before transitioning to Hollywood in the early 1930s. She signed with Warner Bros. and quickly gained attention for her performances in films like "Of Human Bondage" (1934), which earned her critical acclaim.

Davis received numerous accolades throughout her career, including two Academy Awards for Best Actress. She won her first Oscar for her role in "Dangerous" (1935) and her second for "Jezebel" (1938). She was nominated for the Oscar ten times in total, a record she shares with Katharine Hepburn.

Davis was known for portraying strong, complex female characters. Some of her most memorable roles include Margo Channing in "All About Eve" (1950), Charlotte Vale in "Now, Voyager" (1942), and Baby Jane Hudson in "What Ever Happened to Baby Jane?" (1962).

Davis was known for her outspoken nature and clashed with studio executives and co-stars throughout her career. Her feud with actress Joan Crawford, which reached its peak during the filming of "What Ever Happened to Baby Jane?," is legendary in Hollywood lore.

Despite facing challenges in the latter part of her career, Davis continued to act in films, television, and theater. She received numerous honors and awards for her contributions to the entertainment industry. Her impact on cinema and her status as an icon of the silver screen continue to be celebrated long after her passing in 1989.

Bette Davis left an indelible mark on Hollywood with her talent, charisma, and dedication to her craft. She remains an enduring figure in the history of cinema, remembered for her remarkable performances and lasting legacy.

name: Greta Garbo
description:
Greta Garbo was a Swedish-born actress who became one of the most iconic and enigmatic stars of Hollywood's Golden Age. Born Greta Lovisa Gustafsson on September 18, 1905, in Stockholm, Sweden, she rose to fame in the silent film era and successfully transitioned to talkies, leaving an indelible mark on cinema history. Here are some key points about Greta Garbo and her career:

 Garbo began her acting career in Swedish silent films in the 1920s. Her breakthrough came with the film "The Saga of Gosta Berling" (1924), directed by Mauritz Stiller. Stiller played a significant role in shaping Garbo's early career and guiding her transition to Hollywood.

Garbo was discovered by MGM studio executive Louis B. Mayer, who brought her to Hollywood in 1925. She quickly became a sensation with American audiences, known for her striking beauty, intense performances, and unique screen presence. Her first major Hollywood film was "Torrent" (1926).

 Garbo starred in several successful silent films, including "Flesh and the Devil" (1926) and "Love" (1927), opposite leading man John Gilbert. Their on-screen chemistry and romantic pairings captivated audiences worldwide.

 Unlike many silent film stars who struggled with the transition to talkies, Garbo's career flourished in the sound era. Her first talking film, "Anna Christie" (1930), showcased her talent for dramatic dialogue and earned her an Academy Award nomination for Best Actress.

Garbo is best remembered for her roles in classic films such as "Mata Hari" (1931), "Grand Hotel" (1932), "Queen Christina" (1933), and "Camille" (1936). Her performances often portrayed complex, independent women grappling with love, desire, and societal expectations.

 Garbo's last film role was in "Two-Faced Woman" (1941), after which she retired from acting at the age of 35. She lived a reclusive life in New York City, rarely granting interviews or making public appearances. Her withdrawal from the spotlight only added to her mystique and legend.

Greta Garbo remains one of the most celebrated and iconic actresses in film history. Her beauty, talent, and enigmatic persona continue to fascinate audiences and inspire generations of actors. She received an Honorary Academy Award in 1955 for her unforgettable screen performances.

name: Ben Kenobi

He is able to use a mysterious power called the Force and has a rare weapon not seen often in the days of the Galactic Empire, a lightsaber.

name: Darth Vader
description: A mysterious villain covered in black armor and a mask to help him breath, Darth Vader is the Dark Lord of the Sith and only answers to the Emperor himself. He is imposing and has no remorse for what he does to preserve the Galactic Empire's rule. Vader is able to use the Force for his evil methods and has a red lightsaber.

name: Wilhuff Tarkin
description: Having achieved the rank of Grand Moff in the Galactic Empire, Tarkin answers to no one except for the Emperor. He has total control over the Galactic Empire's new weapon, the Death Star, and is not afraid to use it to snuff out the Rebel Alliance. He is responsible for the destruction of Princess Leia's homeworld, Alderaan. Tarkin meets his end when he refuses to leave the Death Star as it comes under attack, over-confidently believing that it is indestructible.

name: Owen Lars
description: Moisture farmer and uncle to Luke Skywalker. With his wife, Beru, he will do anything to keep Luke safe on Tatooine, even if it means coming across as mean and gruff. He unfortunately gets killed by the Galactic Empire in their search for the stolen Death Star plans.

name: Beru Lars
description: Moisture farmer and aunt to Luke Skywalker. With her husband, Owen, her goal is to keep Luke safe on Tatooine. Beru keeps the Lars Homestead tidy and makes meals for the family. She unfortunately gets killed by the Galactic Empire in their search for the stolen Death Star plans.

name: Rocky Balboa

The heavyweight championship of the world is going to be fought on Jan. 1, 1976, to kick off the Bicentennial year in the nation’s cradle. To nearly everyone’s surprise, the unassuming and unheralded Rocky is going to be the challenger.

name: Apollo Creed

name: Mrs. Gump

name: Benjamin Buford "Bubba" Blue
description: Benjamin Buford "Bubba" Blue and Forrest Gump met when Forrest Gump went to Vietnam. They were in the same platoon. Unfortunately, "Bubba" died in Vietnam but left an impression on Forrest Gump. Years later, Forrest Gump and Lieutenant Dan start a shrimp boat company and name it after him; "Bubba Gump Shrimp Company". Benjamin Buford "Bubba" Blue is portrayed by Mykelti Williamson.

name: Lieutenant Dan Taylor
description: Lieutenant Dan Taylor is the platoon leader when Forrest Gump enters the Vietnam War. Forrest Gump saves his life however, Lieutenant Dan loses both legs in the process. Lieutenant Dan Taylor is portrayed by Gary Sinise and was nominated for Best Supporting Actor in the 1995 Academy Awards.

name: Jenny Curran
description: Jenny Curran is the childhood friend of Forrest Gump. She loves Forrest Gump. Portrayed by Robin Wright.

name: Forrest Gump
description: A man with physical and mental limitations that lives a simple yet fulfilling life. Portrayed by Tom Hanks who won the 1995 Academy Award for Best Actor for his portrayal of Forrest Gump.

name: Andy Dufresne
description: A banker sentenced to life in prison in 1947 for the murder of his wife and her lover. He is very smart and uses this to his advantage making friends with other prisoner and gaining the trust of the warden and the guards.

name: Ellis Boyd "Red" Redding
description:
A lifelong convict, "Red" is the only one at Shawshank Prison that doesn’t deny committing the murder he is accused of, saying he’s the “only guilty man in Shawshank.”  Even though he is in prison, "Red" believes that he will never get out and makes the best of his time while at Shawshank Prison.
Ellis Boyd "Red" Redding is portrayed by Morgan Freeman.

name: C-3PO
description: A protocol droid whose main purpose is to assist humans with translating language. Best friends with R2-D2. Very eager to assist in his areas of strength, he is very nervous of going on adventures and being put in harm's way.

name: R2-D2
description: An astromech droid who has been tasked with an important mission. Best friends with C-3PO, he is the one in the duo who is more willing to take risks and find creative ways to solve problems.

name: Imperial Stormtrooper
description: The most common soldier in the Galactic Empire, they are on the frontlines of every conflict throughout the galaxy. Not known for their accuracy with a blaster rifle.

name: Jack Harper
description: A technician who works to repair drones on Earth and questions why the humans have to leave Earth if they won the war with the aliens. Jack is filled with curiosity and not a rule follower. Because of this, Jack seeks the truth behind his dreams and memories. Jack Harper is portrayed by Tom Cruise.

name: Malcolm Beech
description: Malcolm Beech is a survivor of the war and referred to as a "scav". He teaches, enlightens, and guides Jack Harper towards to understand the truth behind his memories. Malcolm Beech is portrayed by Morgan Freeman.

name: Julia Rusakova Harper
description:
Julia Rusakova Harper, Jack's wife and a Russian crew member on the Odyssey mission. Her return to Earth is eye-opening to Jack Harper since she has been just a faded memory from decades ago.
Julia Rusakova Harper is portrayed by Olga Kurylenko.

name: Victoria "Vika"
description: Victoria "Vika" Olsen, is Jack's communications partner and housemate. They are a couple until the return to Earth of Julia makes Jack and "Vika" question what is real.  "Vika" is a rule follower and an opposite to Jack. She questions nothing and simply follows the rules. Victoria "Vika" Olsen is portrayed by Andrea Riseborough.

name: Dr. William "Will" Rodman
description:
Dr. William "Will" Rodman, is a scientist trying to find a cure for Alzheimer's disease. His father has the disease and "Will" has the opportunity to test his drug on a chimpanzee named Caesar.  Through trial and error, the drug is successful and Caesar becomes incredible intelligent.
Dr. William "Will" Rodman is portrayed by James Franco.

name: Charles Rodman
description: Charles Rodman is Will's father. He is a former music teacher who is battling Alzheimer's disease. Soon, his disease improves when his son gives him an experimental drug which was also given to the laboratory chimpanzees. But that's where the similarities end. Charles Rodman is portrayed by John Lithgow.

name: Caesar
description:
Caesar is a lab chimpanzee that receives an experimental drug and becomes highly intelligent beginning a chain of events that will change history.
Caesar is portrayed by Andy Serkis via performance capture technology.

name: Malcolm
description: Malcolm is the human equivalent of the chimpanzee leader, Caesar. A former architect, Malcolm is the leader of a small group of humans. He is the husband of Ellie and the father of Alexander. Malcolm is portrayed by Jason Clarke.

name: Ellie
description: Ellie was a nurse at the U.S. Center for Disease Control. She studied the disease and discovered that humans who were not killed by the flu were genetically immune. Ellie is portrayed by Keri Russell.

name: Dreyfus
description: Dreyfus is an ex-police officer and the leader of the remaining human survivors. Dreyfus is portrayed by Gary Oldman.

name: The Colonel
description: The Colonel is the leader of the paramilitary faction the Alpha-Omega. The Colonel is portrayed by Woody Harrelson.

name: Christopher Smith / Peacemaker
description: A not-so-smart but well-meaning superhero. Peacemaker will achieve his goals at any cost even if it goes against anything he holds dear (peace). Not a "people person", his best friend is a bald eagle named Eagly.  Peacemaker is portrayed by John Cena.

name: Leota Adebayo
description: The daughter of A.R.G.U.S. leader Amanda Waller and a member of Project Butterfly. Although part of Peacemaker's team, she does not agree with anything Peacemaker does.  Leota Adebayo is portrayed by Danielle Brooks.

name: Adrian Chase / Vigilante
description:
Adrian Chase / Vigilante is a self-proclaimed crimefighter. He is desperate to make friends with anyone and is thrilled to meet and be part of Peacemaker's team.  Vigilante is a foolish sociopath, willing to kill any lawbreaker.
Adrian Chase / Vigilante is portrayed by Freddie Stroma

name: Barbie
description: Barbie is a 64-year-old fashion model and cultural icon who has been at the forefront of American pop culture for decades. Known as a fashion queen who has embraced a variety of styles and outfits over the decades, Barbie has also had a remarkably diverse career history throughout her life, working in more than 250 different professions.

name: Ken
description:
Kenneth Sean "Ken" Carson Jr. is a fashion doll introduced by American toy company Mattel in 1961 as the counterpart of Barbie, who had been introduced two years earlier.

Similar to Barbie, Ken is from Willows, Wisconsin, and has a fashionable line of clothing and accessories (although he made his debut wearing only a swimsuit). In the Barbie mythos, Ken met Barbie on the set of a TV commercial and is her boyfriend, per promotional box inscriptions from his debut until 2018. As of September 2022, he is perceived as one of Barbie's main friends. Since his debut, Ken has held over 40 occupations, the latest being "beach" (standing in the sand and surveying the waves), as depicted in the 2023 Barbie film.

name: Percy Jackson
description: Percy Jackson is a young demigod with sea-green eyes, unruly dark hair, and a determined yet curious expression. He exudes confidence and carries himself with a sense of adventure, often dressed in practical attire suitable for outdoor exploration. His appearance reflects a blend of ordinary features and subtle hints of his divine heritage, embodying the essence of a hero destined for extraordinary quests.

name: Annabeth Chase
description: Annabeth Chase is a key character in the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series. With her blonde hair, stormy gray eyes, and an air of intelligence, she embodies a blend of beauty and brains. Annabeth is known for her sharp wit, strategic mind, and extensive knowledge of Greek mythology. She is fiercely loyal to her friends, particularly Percy Jackson, and displays bravery and determination in the face of danger. As a natural leader, Annabeth often takes charge during quests, relying on her resourcefulness and independence to overcome challenges. Despite her tough exterior, she also exhibits compassion and empathy towards others, making her a well-rounded and compelling character in the series.

name: Grover Underwood
description: Grover Underwood is a loyal and compassionate satyr from the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series. With his curly hair, scruffy beard, and a pair of furry legs poking out from his pants, Grover's appearance betrays his nature as a satyr. Despite his initial timidness, Grover displays unexpected bravery and determination when protecting his friends, especially Percy Jackson. His sense of humor adds a light-hearted touch to the group's adventures, while his resourcefulness and connection with nature make him an invaluable ally. Grover's innocence, naivety, and unwavering loyalty make him a beloved character in the series.

name: Luke Castellan
description: Luke Castellan is a charismatic and intelligent demigod from the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series. With his handsome features and silver eyes that hint at his divine heritage as a son of Hermes, Luke initially appears as a loyal friend and ally to Percy Jackson and others at Camp Half-Blood. However, beneath his charming exterior lies a complex character driven by deep-seated resentment towards the Olympian gods. As the series progresses, Luke's ambition and thirst for power lead him down a path of betrayal, ultimately aligning himself with the Titans in their quest to overthrow Olympus. Despite his tragic descent into darkness, Luke's character serves as a reminder of the complexities of human nature and the dangers of unchecked ambition.

name: Sally Jackson
description: Sally Jackson is depicted as a caring and devoted mother in the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series. With her warm smile and nurturing demeanor, she embodies the essence of maternal love and protection. Sally is described as having a kind face framed by gentle features, with eyes that reflect both wisdom and compassion. Despite facing challenges as a single mother, she radiates inner strength and resilience, always putting her son Percy's well-being above all else.

name: Poseidon
description: Poseidon embodies the immense strength and authority of the sea, with a presence that commands respect and awe. He is depicted as majestic and imposing, with a regal demeanor befitting his divine status. His appearance is often described as commanding, with rugged handsomeness and piercing eyes that reflect the depths of the ocean. Despite his godly stature, Poseidon is also characterized by his deep love and concern for his demigod son, Percy Jackson. He watches over Percy from afar, intervening to aid him when necessary and guiding Percy through subtle signs and messages. Poseidon's paternal instincts shine through in his interactions with Percy, demonstrating a protective and nurturing side to his character.

name: Zeus
description: Zeus embodies the formidable might and majesty of the sky and thunder, with a presence that demands respect and reverence. He is often depicted as regal and imposing, with a stern demeanor that reflects his authority as the king of the gods. As the ruler of Olympus, Zeus is characterized by his sense of duty and responsibility towards maintaining order and justice in the divine realm. He takes his role as a leader seriously, enforcing the laws of the gods and overseeing the affairs of both mortals and immortals.

name: Hades
description: Hades, the god of the underworld, is depicted as brooding and imposing, with a presence that commands respect and awe. He rules over the realm of the dead with stern authority, overseeing the souls of the departed and maintaining order in the afterlife. Despite his ominous reputation, Hades is not portrayed as inherently evil in the series and is instead depicted as a complex and multifaceted character. While he can be stern and imposing, he also exhibits moments of vulnerability and humanity, particularly in his interactions with his wife, Persephone, and other gods.

name: Ares
description: Ares is portrayed as a formidable and hot-headed figure, embodying the brutal and chaotic aspects of warfare. He is depicted as muscular and imposing, with a fierce and aggressive demeanor that reflects his domain over battle and conflict. In the series, Ares serves as both an antagonist and a reluctant ally to Percy Jackson and his friends. He embodies the traits of a typical war god: ruthless, ambitious, and driven by a desire for power and conquest. Ares frequently clashes with Percy and other characters, often acting as a catalyst for conflict and chaos.

name: Clarisse La Rue
description: Clarisse La Rue is a dynamic and multi-dimensional character in the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series, embodying the complexities of strength, loyalty, and personal growth amidst the challenges of being a demigod. Her presence adds depth and richness to the world of Camp Half-Blood, showcasing the diversity of personalities among its inhabitants.

name: Medusa
description: Medusa is cursed with a horrifying appearance, which includes a head full of live snakes in place of hair, sharp fangs, and a gaze that petrifies anyone who meets her eyes. Despite her frightening appearance, Medusa is sometimes portrayed as a tragic figure. Once a beautiful woman, her transformation into a monster is seen as punishment for her actions or as a result of divine jealousy. This tragic backstory adds depth to her character, evoking sympathy and pity from some interpretations of her tale.

name: Mr. D / Dionysus
description: In the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series, Dionysus, also known as Mr. D, serves as the director of Camp Half-Blood. He is depicted as a sarcastic, disgruntled, and somewhat lazy character who resents his duties at the camp due to being punished by Zeus. Despite his gruff exterior, he occasionally shows moments of insight and wisdom, revealing hidden depths beneath his outwardly apathetic demeanor. Dionysus adds humor and complexity to the series with his unique personality and unconventional leadership style.

name: Chiron
description: Chiron is a central and beloved character in the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series, embodying the qualities of wisdom, compassion, and courage that define a true hero and mentor. His guidance and leadership play a crucial role in shaping the destinies of Percy and his friends as they face the challenges of their divine heritage.

name: Athena
description: Athena is a multifaceted and complex character in Greek mythology, embodying the ideals of wisdom, strength, and integrity. Her presence in the "Percy Jackson & the Olympians" series adds depth and richness to the world of Camp Half-Blood, reflecting her enduring significance in both ancient and modern culture.

name: Mama
description: A female parent

name: Princess
description: An important female member of a royal family, especially a daughter or granddaughter of a king and queen, or the wife of a prince.

name: Miller
description: A miller is a person who operates or manages a mill, which is a facility used for grinding grains into flour.

name: Scavengers
description: These common and small bug enemies appear in large groups. At lower levels, they can be taken out with any weapon, but as you progress, consider using more powerful weapons and Stratagems to deal with them. Their main role is to attract stronger Terminids to your location.

name: Warriors
description: Found alongside Scavengers, Warriors attack in groups. They form the backbone of the bug forces. The Warrior is a lightly armored, medium-sized Terminid that can appear on any difficulty. They appear to be a juvenile Brood Commander. They are slower than Scavengers and Hunters, and attempt to attack Helldivers with their claws. Warriors are also able to survive for a few seconds after losing their head, during which they will rush forward, swinging their claws wildly.

name: Hunters
description: The Hunter is a medium-sized Terminid that appears on Medium difficulty and higher. They appear to be adult Pouncers. Hunters use their wings to approach and dodge incoming fire, and attack using its claws and stylets (tongue). Hunters will also attempt to separate themselves from swarms to flank Helldivers. Hunters can also cause a Bug Breach, allowing more Terminids to spawn. On Challenging difficulty and higher, the Hunter's stylets will also slow Helldivers down, leaving them vulnerable.

name: Stalkers
description: The Stalker is a medium-sized Terminid that can first appear on Easy difficulty, spawning from Stalker Lairs. Super Earth Propaganda claims that Stalkers are mutated Hunters with camouflage capabilities and enhanced strength. There are reports that this strain of Terminid appeared during the First Galactic War, but there is no evidence that they had camouflage capabilities before. Stalkers slowly approach Helldivers while camouflaged and ambush using their claws or stylets when close; if unsuccessful, they will briefly retreat before resuming their hunt. Destroying all Stalker Lairs will stop Stalkers from spawning for the rest of the mission.

name: Bile Spewers
description: The Bile Spewer is a moderately armored, medium-sized Terminid that can appear on Medium difficulty and higher. They appear to be a mature Bile Spitter with an enlarged abdomen. Bile Spewers spit streams of highly corrosive acid called "Bile", which can slow down and can prove fatal to a Helldiver if they are exposed to a full stream. Diving out of the way when it rears its head for this attack is advised. On Extreme difficulty and higher, Bile Spewers gain the ability to fire a volley of bile into the air, similar to a mortar. This greatly increases the Bile Spewer's range and lethality.

name: Bile Titans
description: The Bile Titan is a massive, heavily armored Terminid that appears to be the final growth stage of a Bile Warrior. They can be found on Challenging difficulty as an Elimination Target and begin to spawn naturally and more frequently as difficulty increases. Despite its size, it can quickly catch up to Helldivers, spewing its lethal bile onto them. Helldivers near it can also be crushed or speared by its hulking claws.

name: Chargers
description: The Charger is a large, heavily armored Terminid that can first appear on Medium difficulty as an Elimination Target or sometimes guarding the Shuttle Bay in Emergency Evacuation. It spawns naturally and more frequently as difficulty increases. Living up to their name, Chargers charge at Helldivers in an attempt to bash or trample them, dealing a significant amount of damage. This can concuss and potentially launch Helldivers. Chargers will also use their claws at close range.

name: Brood Commanders
description: Named after the strain of Terminids that existed during the First Galactic War, the Brood Commander is a heavily armored and dangerous Terminid that is a variant of the Warrior and a member of the nearly-extinct Terminid Leadership Cast.

name: Shriekers
description: The Shrieker is a flying Terminid with large wings that engage in hit-and-run tactics, diving in to attack Helldivers before flying back up to the skies. Shriekers appeared following an evolution among the ranks of the Terminids. They are capable of flight, making them a severe threat to Super Earth's democratic forces. They only spawn at Shrieker Nests if one is present and undestroyed, and otherwise do not appear in Missions. They are medium/small-sized bugs with a massive wingspan. They have brown medium armor and orange accents.

name: Elites
description: The Elite is much like the Warrior but with heavier armor and more durability. Their armor serves them well and good aim as well as armor-piercing ammunition are recommended.

name: Impalers
description: The Impaler is a very different threat compared to the other bugs, it burrows its head in the ground and tunnels its tentacles so that they burst from the ground close to its target. The tentacles are very dangerous but the creature also exposes a weak point when burrowing them, something that implies a lack of self-preservation.

name: Behemoths
description: Behemoth is a large, heavily armored Terminid that is a variation of the Charger that has more armor and is easily distinguishable from the normal charger by its elongated horn/tusk-like armor on its head. They are found solely on Medium difficulty as the Elimination Target or sometimes guarding the Shuttle Bay in Emergency Evacuation.

name: Hive Lords
description: The Bug Hive Lord is an enemy capable of creating new tunnels for the Bug hives and will if left alone, perforate the entire crust of a planet with tunnels. As they are mostly underground, they are exceptionally hard to attack and get rid of. Therefore, any opportunity to assault a Hive Lord should not be squandered, and as they are extremely dangerous, bring the best you have when assaulting them.

name: Troopers
description: The primary infantry unit of the Automaton forces, the Trooper is the most basic Automaton unit that can be fielded in larger numbers and can be equipped veritable number of equipment or weapons based on mission parameters. They are considered the cannon fodder of the Automaton forces as they're the easiest to eliminate when in small numbers, however, they can be quite formidable when grouped into a horde. There are currently 5 different types of troopers: Trooper - Automaton infantry equipped with assault rifles. Brawler - Automaton infantry equipped with dual-energy blades, unable to engage in ranged attacks outside of manning machine gun emplacements. Raider - Automaton infantry equipped with machine guns. Rocket Raider - Automaton infantry equipped with a rocket launcher. Marauder - Automaton infantry equipped with Rapid-Fire Cannons. Assault - Automaton infantry equipped with a Jump Pack, pistol and energy blade.

name: Commissars
description: The Commissar is a unique bot responsible for calling in bot drops as a first action. (Other infantry are also capable of calling in bot drops). Helldivers are advised to keep their eyes sharp and gun down the Commissars before they can launch their signal flares, especially on higher difficulty missions where Bot Drops can easily bring in sufficient number of heavily armed socialists to overwhelm the team.

name: Berserkers
description: Berserkers are reliant on melee attacks and slower than other Automatons. However, they do tend to group up. Their weak spots are their head and the stomach area. Shotguns, grenades, or armor-piercing weapons are effective against them.

name: Dropships
description: Packed to the brim with robotic infantry, Dropships conduct rapid deployment of Automaton units
